{"title": "Recollections of Napoleon at St. Helena", "description": "In this memoir written by Betsy Balcombe, who was a precocious 14 year old at the time of events, we are provided with a rare account of the character, the moods and humanity of Napoleon Bonaparte.\nShe recalls her initial shock and fear at the arrival of the famous, exiled prisoner on the remote Island of St. Helena where she and her family resided. And how surprised she was when Napoleon decided he wanted to live with them at \"the Briars\" until his home in Longwood would be made ready for him. She relates from memory how she came to think of him as a friend, a delightful companion, and a remarkable man. - Summary by Celine Major", "duration": 12685, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "15445", "name": "Elizabeth Balcombe Abell"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/recollectionsofnapoleon_2011_librivox/napoleon_2011.jpg", "copyright_year": "1844", "genres": ["*Non-fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Celine Major"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Celine Major"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Helen Z. Ferrara"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface", "readers": [11697], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/recollectionsofnapoleon_2011_librivox/recollectionsofnapoleon_00_balcombe_64kb.mp3", "duration": 148}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapters 1 - 3", "readers": [11697], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/recollectionsofnapoleon_2011_librivox/recollectionsofnapoleon_01_balcombe_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1410}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapters 4-5", "readers": [11697], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/recollectionsofnapoleon_2011_librivox/recollectionsofnapoleon_02_balcombe_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1304}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapters 6-7", "readers": [11697], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/recollectionsofnapoleon_2011_librivox/recollectionsofnapoleon_03_balcombe